<h3>Explanation:</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>HTML Structure</strong>: The calculator is structured with a display input field and a grid of buttons for numbers, operators, and actions (clear, equals).</li>
<li><strong>CSS Styling</strong>: The calculator is centered on the page with a clean, modern design. Buttons are styled with hover effects, and different colors are used to distinguish between numbers, operators, and actions.</li>
<li><strong>JavaScript Functions</strong>: The <code>appendNumber</code>, <code>appendOperator</code>, <code>clearDisplay</code>, and <code>calculate</code> functions handle the logic for updating the display and performing calculations.</li>
</ul>
